The paper deals with a problem related to packing items into a knapsack, which is a classic problem in computer science. The use of policies and algorithms to solve the problem suggests that it belongs to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of the factor of the optimum packing and the complexity of deciding whether a given policy achieves a certain factor suggests that it also belongs to the category of game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of universal policies and the analysis of their efficiency suggest that it belongs to the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the study of the complexity of the problem suggests that it belongs to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
